Model Background

Model Background

bh

2021-11-03





bayesian Occupancey Model


Model:



   Z(i) ~ Bernoulli(Psi(i))


   y(i,j) ~ Bernoulli(Z(i) * p(i,j))



&



   logit(Psi(i)) = beta0 + beta1 * site cov 1 + … linear model on site covs

   logit(p(i,j)) = alpha0 + alpha1 * rep cov 1 … linear model on rep covs (and possibly site covs)




where:



   i = site

   j = replicate

   Psi = occupancy rate

   p = detection rate

   Z = latent occupancy state (1/0)

   y = data – capture history



Occupancy is expected to vary across years, since a new site was surveyed each season

year is accounted for as a covariate on Psi


Detection rates are assumed to not significanly vary over seasons (by species)





Residuals:


from towards data science


basic assumption of the model is that residuals are Independent and normally distributed


Residuals can be defined multiple ways in a hierarchical model


for example, Raw Residuals:


fitted Residuals:



   rsite = Z(i) - Psi(i)

   rrep = y(i,j) - Z(i) * p(i,j) (full model residuals)



simulate Residuals:



   rsite.sim = (Z(i))sim - Psi(i)

   rrep.sim = (y(i,j))sim - Z(i) * p(i,j) (full model residuals)



Baysean p value = fraction of simulated residuals < median fitted residuals





Dharma rediduals


from Dharma documentation




Dharma residuals on occupancy model:


model:


   Z(i) ~ Bernoulli(Psi(i))


   y(i,j) ~ Bernoulli(Z(i) * p(i,j))


    1. build and run the model


    2. simulate y and Z 1000 times from the model (conditional on all parameters..)


    3. use the dharma package to get residuals for the detection and occupancy levels of the model:

       a. detection residuals: supply ydata, and y1000Simulations to Dharma

       b. occupancy residuals: supply Zdata, and Z1000Simulations to Dharma

         note: Zdata = ydata collapsed to 1/0 detection/no detection by site
